summary:
I was born and raised in Thessaloniki, Greece. In my childhood, I was obsessed with Greek mythology and Jackie Gaff's 'I Wonder Why' book series. Books opened up the world to me, fed my imagination, and sparked my curiosity and interest in learning. In many ways I'm more of a generalist, carrying a suitcase packed with wide-ranging experiences. 

I have gained experience coordinating and supervising people and activities. I enjoy playing the part of a spider in the web within a team. The fact that I have a critical and analytical mentality, combined with written communication skills, helps me in that position. 

I set great store by independence and freedom. I feel comfortable organising my work myself. With my helpful mentality, I enjoy working with and for people. It is important to me that my work is relevant to society.

My background includes: event production | archiving project | coordinating volunteers | teaching music | qualitative research | Musicology and Music Pedagogy BA | Arts, Culture and Society MA

As I move forward, I aim to focus on: conducting research | drafting | knowledge-sharing | advisory processes | working with multiple stakeholders | EU funding

For more information, please do not hesitate to contact me by adding me on LinkedIn or send me an email at atkardam[at]gmail[dot]com.
